cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and temporal annotation. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a tool for automated analysis and validation of temporal annotations. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the tool uses statistical analysis to identify linguistic features. It may also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the analysis of text corpora. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the development of a tool that can aid in the analysis of language use in society.
